<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="5" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Marshal <persName corresp="#p_S16" type="to">Stalin</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d5fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché,
                                Moscow, via Navy channels.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<hi rend="smallcaps">Pearl Harbor,
                                    Hawaii</hi>,] <lb/>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-27">27 July
                                1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Number 32. Top Secret and Personal. For Marshal <persName corresp="#p_S16">Stalin</persName> from the President.</p>
                        <pb facs="0087" n="5" xml:id="pg_5"/>
                        <p>I can fully understand the difficulty of your coming to a conference with
                            the Prime Minister and me in view of the rapid military progress now
                            being made but I hope you can keep such a conference very much in mind
                            and that we can meet as early as possible. Such a meeting would help me
                            domestically and we are approaching the time for further strategical
                            decisions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>